# Copy to `.dev.vars` — secrets the Worker reads in local dev (miniflare).
# Non-secret config (NEON_AUTH_URL, ADMIN_EMAILS, LIBBY_LIBRARY_KEY) lives in
# wrangler.jsonc `vars`, not here.

# Neon pooled connection string (same value as DATABASE_URL in .env).
DATABASE_URL="postgresql://user:password@ep-xxxx-pooler.region.aws.neon.tech/dbname?sslmode=require"

# --- Optional integrations ---------------------------------------------------

# Scrape-assist runs entirely on free, keyless, open sources by default:
#   books → Open Library · movies/TV → Wikidata (CC0) · TV episodes → TVmaze (CC BY-SA)
# TMDB is an OPTIONAL richer fallback only; its free tier is non-commercial.
# Leave this unset to stay fully open-source.
# TMDB_API_KEY=""

# Bulk-import tooling. Shared secret authorizing POST /api/batch/import (used by
# `npm run media:bulk` and cron). Leave unset to disable the endpoint (501).
# Generate one: `openssl rand -hex 32`
# BATCH_TOKEN=""
# BATCH_USER_ID=""   # optional: attribute batch/cron imports to this user id

# Billing (Stripe). Leave unset to keep billing dormant (endpoints return 501).
# Create a recurring $1.99/mo price in Stripe, then fill all three:
# STRIPE_SECRET_KEY="sk_test_..."
# STRIPE_PRICE_STANDARD="price_..."          # the Standard plan price id
# STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET="whsec_..."          # from `stripe listen` (dev) or the dashboard
